[{"id":"VR831719","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"direction_paragraph\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">Show all your work for each part of the the question. The parts within the question may not have equal weight.</p><br/><div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a cylindrical container with a lid on top. The lid is in the shape of a disk that has a larger radius than the cylindrical container. The cylindrical container has height h.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR831719.g02.svg\"/></div>\n<p class=\"passage_para\">A cylinder with cross-sectional area <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>A</mi></math></span></span> and height <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"h\"><math alttext=\"h\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>h</mi></math></span></span> has a lid with mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> on top, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. There are <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N\"><math alttext=\"N\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>N</mi></math></span></span> atoms of an ideal gas inside the cylinder. The lid rests on top of the cylinder and is not attached to the cylinder. The pressure outside the cylinder is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P sub atmosphere\"><math alttext=\"P sub atmosphere\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mi>atm</mi></msub></math></span></span>.</p>\n</div></div></div></div><div class=\"item_part part_id:A part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"A\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(a) The gas in the cylinder is slowly heated and it increases in temperature. When it reaches a certain temperature, the lid accelerates upward and loses contact with the cylinder. <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Indicate</span> why this happens. <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Justify</span> your reasoning in terms of the interaction between the atoms of gas and the lid.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR831719_rubric"},{"id":"VR831719","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:B part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"B\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(b) <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Derive</span> an expression for the minimum temperature of the gas that would result in the lid accelerating upward in terms of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>A</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"h\"><math alttext=\"h\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>h</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"N\"><math alttext=\"N\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>N</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P sub atmosphere\"><math alttext=\"P sub atmosphere\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mtext>atm</mtext></msub></math></span></span>, and physical constants, as appropriate.</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR831719_rubric"},{"id":"VR831719","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"item_part part_id:C part_name:ExtendedText response_class:FreeResponse response_type:Essay\" id=\"C\"><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">(c) Immediately after the lid loses contact with the cylinder, a small gap exists between the lid and the cylinder. Very shortly after the lid loses contact with the cylinder, the lid falls back to its original position. <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Indicate</span> the process that is responsible for this. <span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Justify</span> your response by referring to the equation derived in part (b).</p></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR831719_rubric"}]